This paper deals with the problem of coded caching, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves the optimization of delivery strategies for a network, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The formulation of the problem as a combinatorial optimization problem suggests that it could also be classified under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of approximation algorithms and analysis of approximation ratios is a common technique in theoretical computer science, which could place this paper under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) or machine learning (cs.LG).
